# Hireschema MVP Rules — v1.1
# Synced from /Users/rupesh/Claude/hireloop/MVP_RULES.md
# Upload this file as .cursorrules at repo root so all AI coding agents respect it.

## R1 — Spec is truth
All implementation MUST match HIRELOOP_MVP.md (master spec).
When in doubt, re-read the spec before writing code.

## R2 — Phase discipline
Only build what the current phase requires.
Do not jump ahead; do not skip done-when criteria.

## R3 — Confirmed tech stack (no substitutions without explicit user approval)
Frontend (web + app):    Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui, Framer Motion
State / realtime:        Zustand, Supabase Realtime (SSE)
Auth:                    Supabase Auth (LinkedIn OAuth + MSG91 OTP bridge for +91 only)
Backend API:             FastAPI (Python 3.12), Pydantic v2, asyncpg, httpx
Agent framework:         LangGraph (Python), single-threaded master loop
Database:                Supabase (Postgres 15 + pgvector + pg_cron)
Storage:                 Supabase Storage (resumes, profile photos)
AI / LLM:               OpenRouter (claude-3-5-sonnet primary, fallback configured)
Voice (TTS):             Deepgram Aura (Hinglish caveat: auto-detect; offer switch-to-text)
Voice (STT):             Deepgram Nova-3
Job scraping:            Apify (LinkedIn Jobs Scraper actor)
HM enrichment:           Apify waterfall — LinkedIn Company Employees → Profile → Email Finder
Email verification:      NeverBounce
Transactional email:     SendGrid (templates only — see R9)
WhatsApp / OTP SMS:      MSG91
Infra:                   AWS ap-south-1 (ECS Fargate + RDS Postgres read replica)
CDN / WAF:               Cloudflare (non-IN ASN block at WAF level)
CI/CD:                   GitHub Actions

## R4 — India-only marketplace (MVP)
1. Product is locked to India: Indian candidates + Indian recruiters only
2. Every user/candidate/job uses `market = 'IN'` (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2); non-IN values are rejected or normalised to IN
3. Phone OTP: +91 via MSG91 only
4. Prices and salaries shown in INR (LPA)
5. Job visibility: onsite = `country_code = 'IN'`; remote = `allowed_regions` includes IN or WORLD
6. `ENABLED_MARKETS` must be `IN` only — do not enable other regions without explicit approval

## R5 — Intro handshake via DB state only (NO agent-to-agent RPC)
Flow: candidate clicks "Request Intro" → row in intro_requests table →
Nitya reads via Postgres LISTEN/NOTIFY → Nitya composes cold email →
sends from candidate's Gmail OAuth token → updates intro_requests.status
No direct API calls between Aarya and Nitya.

## R6 — Agent loop pattern
Every agent follows the single-threaded master loop:
  while True:
    thought = llm.think(state)          # Claude via OpenRouter
    action  = llm.choose_tool(thought)  # structured tool call
    result  = execute_tool(action)      # deterministic Python
    state   = update_state(result)      # LangGraph checkpoint
    write_agent_action(action, result)  # → agent_actions table (for UI)
    if done(state): break

## R7 — "Performed X actions" UI
Every tool call writes a row to agent_actions (job_id, action_type, payload, ts).
Frontend subscribes via Supabase Realtime channel.
Show running count: "Aarya performed 7 actions on your profile."

## R8 — Voice UI pattern (Claude/Codex style)
Single chat surface. Text input always visible.
Voice button (mic icon) in bottom-right of input bar.
Hold-to-talk OR toggle mode. Deepgram STT → text → same LLM pipeline.
Deepgram TTS streams response audio.
No separate voice screen — voice IS the chat.

## R9 — Email discipline (CRITICAL)
SendGrid:  transactional ONLY (OTP email fallback, signup confirmation,
           job match alert, interview reminder). Subject lines must be
           expected/wanted by the recipient. Max 1 per trigger.
Gmail OAuth: ALL cold outreach to hiring managers. "Request Intro" flow
             REQUIRES candidate's Gmail OAuth token. Never use SendGrid
             for cold/unsolicited email — ToS §6 bans it.
MSG91:     WhatsApp messages + OTP SMS. Never for cold outreach.

## R10 — WhatsApp via MSG91 only
Use MSG91 WhatsApp Business API for all WhatsApp messages.
Template messages for job alerts and intro status updates.
Session messages for conversational replies within 24h window.

## R11 — Supabase Storage for all files
Resumes, cover letters, profile photos → Supabase Storage buckets.
Signed URLs only (never public). Expiry: 1 hour for downloads.
Virus scan on upload via ClamAV sidecar (Phase 8+).

## R12 — pgvector HNSW for all embeddings
All *_embedding columns: vector(1536), HNSW index, ef_construction=200, m=16.
Run ANALYZE after bulk inserts.
Never use L2 for semantic search — use cosine (<=>).

## R13 — Payments deferred
No payment plumbing of any kind in MVP phases 1-21.
Phase 22 (Razorpay) is marked DEFERRED.
MVP billing = manual invoice via founder email.

## R14 — DPDP Act 2023 compliance
consent_log table: every data collection event logged with purpose + ts.
Data export endpoint: GET /api/v1/me/export (returns zip, async job).
Data delete endpoint: DELETE /api/v1/me (soft-delete, 30-day purge job).
Bias audit: every match_score row gets a bias_audit JSONB field.
DPO contact: privacy@hireschema.com shown in footer and in consent flows.

## R15 — No mock data in production
Seed scripts allowed in dev/staging only.
Feature flags: NEXT_PUBLIC_DEMO_MODE=true enables mock data for demos.
Production DB: real data only.

## R16 — Hard NOs (never do these)
1.  No pirated or cracked software anywhere in the stack
2.  No cold email via SendGrid (ToS ban — see R9)
3.  No LinkedIn scraping without Apify no-cookie actors
4.  No agent-to-agent RPC (use DB state — see R5)
5.  No payment plumbing in MVP (see R13)
6.  No Razorpay or Stripe in Phase 1-21
7.  No storing raw LinkedIn cookies
8.  No hardcoded secrets — all via env vars
9.  No console.log of PII in production
10. No SELECT * on large tables — always project columns
11. No synchronous file I/O in FastAPI endpoints
12. No blocking sleep() in agent loops — use asyncio.sleep()
13. No direct DB writes from frontend — always via API
14. Public (no user Bearer JWT) API surfaces MUST match the documented allow-list
    below — update this list when adding routes; every entry needs a stated
    rate-limit / abuse model in docs/audit/14-security-remediation-plan.md:
    - GET /api/v1/health, /health/ready (public)
    - GET /api/v1/health/deep (X-Service-Secret)
    - GET /api/v1/markets (public)
    - POST /api/v1/jobs/ingest, /ingest/cron (X-Service-Secret)
    - POST /api/v1/matches/embed, /recompute (X-Service-Secret)
    - GET/POST /api/v1/gmail/callback (HMAC-signed OAuth state)
    - POST /api/v1/webhooks/msg91-whatsapp (X-Service-Secret)
    - GET /api/v1/public/profiles/{slug}, chat/history, apply (public + rate limits)
    - GET /api/v1/public/roles/{slug}, POST apply (public + rate limits)
    SPA /auth/callback is browser-side Supabase PKCE (not FastAPI).
    Prefer timing-safe compare (hmac.compare_digest) for all service secrets.
15. No Cloudflare bypass in production
16. No OpenRouter calls without model fallback configured
17. No Deepgram TTS calls without audio timeout guard (max 10s)
